"content": "<h2>A plant that grows in water</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job8:11\">JOB 8:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:1-Gen41:4\">GEN 41:1–41:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:17-Gen41:21\">GEN 41:17–41:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:1-Exod2:6\">EXO 2:1–2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:15\">1KI 14:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job40:21\">JOB 40:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:6\">ISA 19:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:7\">ISA 35:7</a></p>\n<h2>Reeds are weak and fragile plants</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:7\">MAT 11:7</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:24\">LUK 7:24</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:21\">2KI 18:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:6\">ISA 36:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:5\">ISA 58:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:20\">MAT 12:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:3\">ISA 42:3</a></p>\n<h2>Uses of reeds</h2>\n<h3>For fuel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:20\">JOB 41:20</a></strong></p>\n<h3>As measuring rods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:1\">REV 11:1</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The metaphorical use of reeds</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:14-Isa9:15\">ISA 9:14–9:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:14-Isa19:15\">ISA 19:14–19:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek29:6-Ezek29:7\">EZK 29:6–29:7</a></p>",
